# Expanding the Movie Database (Bollywood 2006-2026)

This plan outlines the approach to fulfilling your request to add "all the movies released in years 2006 to 2026 of Bollywood". 

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There are literally **thousands** of Bollywood movies released between 2006 and 2026. We cannot manually hardcode all of these into our JavaScript file, as it would crash your browser and make the website incredibly slow. 
> To do this properly, we must connect the website to a live Movie Database API so it can fetch the movies dynamically as you scroll or search.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> Because we need to fetch thousands of movies, we must use a professional, free API like **TMDB (The Movie Database)**.
> 
> **How would you like to proceed?**
> **Option 1 (Recommended):** You create a free account at [themoviedb.org](https://www.themoviedb.org/) and generate a free "API Key". Once you give me that key, I will rewrite the website's logic to pull *all* the real Bollywood movies from 2006-2026 directly from their servers.
> **Option 2 (Mock Data Expansion):** If you don't want to create an account, I can use my tools to find and hardcode a larger list of the "Top 50" most famous Bollywood movies from that era into our existing mock dataset. It won't be "all" of them, but it will be a much bigger list without needing an API key.

## Proposed Changes (If Option 1 is chosen)

- Add a configuration variable in `script.js` for your TMDB API Key.
- Remove the hardcoded `moviesData` array.
- Write asynchronous JavaScript `fetch()` functions that call the TMDB `/discover/movie` endpoint.
- Configure the API call with parameters: `with_original_language=hi` (Hindi/Bollywood), `region=IN`, and `primary_release_date.gte=2006-01-01`.
- Implement pagination (a "Load More" button or infinite scrolling) so the browser can handle thousands of movies efficiently.

## Verification Plan
- Load the webpage and verify that the API successfully fetches the first page of Bollywood movies from 2006-2026.
- Verify that clicking "Load More" fetches the next set of movies seamlessly.
